        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>
              Summary: El Salvador’s legislative changes increase the
              presidential term against growing accusations of authoritarianism.
            </strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The what:</strong> El Salvador passed legislation that
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-aug-25-spotlight-h2-4-eliminates-presidential-term-limits?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >eliminates presidential term limits</a
            >
            and extends presidential mandates from five to six years. This
            legislation eliminates run-off elections and aligns voting cycles
            for the president and Congress. The reform will also shorten
            President Nayib Bukele’s term by two years, moving general elections
            to March 2027.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The criticism:</strong> Opposition leaders warned about
            growing authoritarianism, weakened democratic checks, and increased
            corruption. Human rights groups condemned the vote's timing, held
            just before a legislative recess and without public debate.
            Lawmakers like Marcela Villatoro called the move a path toward
            clientelism and nepotism.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter: blur(5px)">
            <strong>On the ground:</strong> Bukele’s crackdown on gang violence
            has imprisoned over 2% of the adult population, resulting in reduced
            homicide levels. El Salvador has been under a state of emergency
            since March 2022 and has suspended fundamental rights, including the
            availability of defense counsel. His acceptance of the
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-aug-25-spotlight-h2-5-deportees-from-the-us?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >deportees from the US</a
            >
            to be placed in their mega prison has made him a closer ally to
            Trump.
          </p>
